👨‍💼 Employee Management System (SQL Project)
📌 Project Overview

The Employee Management System (EMS) is a SQL-based database project designed to manage and analyze employee information within an organization. The system stores data related to employees, departments, job roles, salaries, qualifications, leaves, and payroll.

This project demonstrates how SQL and relational databases can be used to efficiently organize HR data and generate insights that support organizational decision-making.

🎯 Objectives

Design a relational database to manage employee-related data.

Maintain data integrity using primary keys and foreign keys.

Store employee details such as job roles, departments, salary, and qualifications.

Track leave records and payroll information.

Perform data analysis using SQL queries to generate HR insights.

🗄️ Database Tables

The Employee Management System contains the following main tables:

1️⃣ JobDepartment

Stores department and job role information.

2️⃣ Employee

Contains employee personal and professional details.

3️⃣ SalaryBonus

Stores salary and bonus information of employees.

4️⃣ Qualification

Tracks employee qualifications and skills.

5️⃣ Leaves

Stores employee leave and absence records.

6️⃣ Payroll

Manages payroll processing and payment information.

🔗 Database Features

Relational database design

Primary key and foreign key relationships

Data integrity and consistency

